<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1938-09-29T11:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1938-09-29T11:00:00-05:00" n="676" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d676">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">760F.62/1309: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Italy</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Phillips</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Rome</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1938-09-29T17:00:00+01:00">September 29, 1938—5
                                    p.m.</date><lb/>[Received September 29—1:20 p.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>274. My telegram No. 268, September 28, 5 p.m. Although I was not
                            afforded an opportunity to present the President’s message to the Duce
                            until nearly 4 p.m. yesterday it may nevertheless be of interest to
                            point out that the Foreign Office and very probably the Duce himself
                            knew before 10 a.m. that such a message had arrived, whereas Lord Perth
                            did not make his first call on Ciano until 10:30.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Phillips</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
